Absolutely, we're entering a new era of engineering where the core of our role truly shines through: solving complex problems, not just stringing together lines of code. Mark Zuckerberg's assertion underscores not a threat but an incredible opportunity.

As problem solvers, we've always been the unsung heroes in transforming raw ideas into reality. Our journey hasn't been about mastering the intricacies of programming languages (though that's certainly a necessary part of the process), but rather about understanding the essence of the challenge